cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper involves the use of deep learning and functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) to identify biomarkers associated with autism spectrum disorder (ASD). Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) as the paper involves image analysis. Neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) are also likely categories as the paper involves the use of deep learning. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category as the paper involves the use of computational methods to understand ASD. Finally, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) is a possible category as the paper involves the interpretation of brain features for clinical applications.
